The paper deals with the problem of phase retrieval, which is a common problem in signal processing and computer vision. The proposed linear spectral estimators (LSPEs) are suitable for general nonlinear measurement systems, which suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also discusses mean-squared error bounds, which is a common topic in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents results on synthetic and real-world phase retrieval problems, which suggests that it could also belong to the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
